{"name":"Divination Sphere","type":"feat","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>You can predict the future and gain information not available to the usual 5 senses.</p><p>When you first gain the Divination sphere, you gain the @UUID[Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.divination.N8cUtvHnNtW2XdP2]{divine} and @UUID[Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.divination.qDemq4OieuMEyO26]{sense} sphere abilities. In addition, you gain a <strong>(divine)</strong> and a <strong>(sense)</strong> talent of your choice. Your first <strong>(divine)</strong> talent does not need to be associated with a sphere that you already possess. The @UUID[Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.divination.dev8rfvHjPajaMvO]{Expanded Divinations} talent grants access to additional alternate divinations.</p><hr /><p>Talents designated as <strong>(divine)</strong> talents grant you additional ways to employ your @UUID[Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.divination.N8cUtvHnNtW2XdP2]{divine} ability, while <strong>(sense)</strong> talents expand your @UUID[Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.divination.qDemq4OieuMEyO26]{sense} ability.</p><p><strong>Alternate Divinations:</strong></p><p>If you possess certain other spheres, you gain additional ways to employ your @UUID[Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.divination.N8cUtvHnNtW2XdP2]{divine} ability. <strong>For each sphere you possess, you also gain one (divine) talent available to that sphere from the list below.</strong> If you already possess all the <strong>(divine)</strong> talents associated with that sphere, you can instead choose another alternate divination in its place, even if you do not possess that sphere. Some talents also require you to possess particular options within that sphere, such as those associated with the Nature sphere requiring certain <strong>geomancy</strong> packages.</p><hr /><p><strong>Alteration Divinations</strong></p><ul><li><p>@UUID[Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.divination.wq1xkpp94aN33TWp]{Detect Monstrosity (divine)}</p></li><li><p>@UUID[Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.d